A vintage 1970s technical illustration showing a massive mainframe computer system with multiple platforms represented as interconnected floating islands, each island depicting a different operating system environment—one with penguin silhouettes suggesting Linux, another with geometric server towers, a third with abstract circuit patterns. Winding code ribbons in muted orange, brown, and olive green flow between the islands, with some ribbons tangled and knotted where they try to cross from one platform to another. The style mimics aged technical manuals with halftone dot patterns, slightly yellowed paper texture, and cross-hatched shading. A lone figure in a lab coat stands on a central observation platform examining the tangled connections through a magnifying glass, surrounded by filing cabinets overflowing with punch cards and documentation scrolls.
